<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="1749" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1749">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 718.1915/226.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Minister of Costa Rica</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-02">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 2, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Minister</hi>: The Department
                            acknowledges, with thanks, the receipt of your note of November 25,
                            1914, with which you enclose a translation of the reply of your
                            Government to the note from the Government of Panama setting forth the
                            reasons which induced the latter not to accept the arbitral award of the
                            Chief Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States, in the Costa
                            Rica-Panama boundary dispute.</p>
                        <p>Both your note and its enclosure have been read with great interest by
                            the Department of State.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>